javaslang

Annotation Type unsafe


  • @Target(value=METHOD)
public @interface unsafe
    Used to mark methods which make certain assumtions regarding types.

    Example:

    List.of(List.of(1)).flatten() returns List.of(1) as expected whereas a call to List.of(1).flatten() does compile but throws at runtime.

    Some powerful Javaslang functionality, like the flatten() method, requires the developer to use it with care. To make this transparent, such functionality is marked as @unsafe.
